  "body": "### Description\nAs part of #4350, we fixed log message about importing a block appearing twice. We know Besu does not actually import block twice but we need to investigate why Besu attempts to import the same block twice and find a mitigation for it.  \n\n\n### Versions \n* Software version: v.22.7.1\n\n### Note\n`MainnetBlockImporter.importBlock` checks if the block is already in the blockchain and will return true if it is already imported.\n\n```\npublic synchronized boolean importBlock(\n      final ProtocolContext context,\n      final Block block,\n      final HeaderValidationMode headerValidationMode,\n      final HeaderValidationMode ommerValidationMode) {\n    if (context.getBlockchain().contains(block.getHash())) {\n      return true;\n    }\n...\n```",
